WEBVTT

00:04.047 --> 00:04.265
.

00:04.308 --> 00:07.181
[upbeat music]

00:07.224 --> 00:09.052
♪

00:09.096 --> 00:11.359
- See?
- I don't know, man.

00:11.402 --> 00:13.839
- What you mean?
That is the best I got.

00:13.883 --> 00:15.189
I spent my whole off day

00:15.232 --> 00:17.539
looking for these
18 different properties.

00:17.582 --> 00:19.628
Just saying, this is Burnside.

00:19.671 --> 00:22.500
It's a little underdeveloped,
lotta crime, but look at that.

00:22.544 --> 00:24.850
- Shoot, I mean, as long
as you get a good deal

00:24.894 --> 00:26.678
through CPD's
real estate program.

00:26.722 --> 00:28.332
- Nah, man,
I just wanna kind of do this

00:28.376 --> 00:30.073
away from the badge, you know?

00:30.117 --> 00:31.596
To do it as me, not as a cop.

00:31.640 --> 00:33.555
- All right, well, then
I'm gonna shoot you straight.

00:33.598 --> 00:35.078
You're gonna spend
all your money.

00:35.122 --> 00:36.340
- Damn right.

00:36.384 --> 00:38.125
And all my time.

00:38.168 --> 00:40.779
- Speaking of time. Mine is up.

00:40.823 --> 00:42.390
I've got a late dinner
with Kim.

00:42.433 --> 00:46.524
- Ah. That explains the shirt.
- [chuckles]

00:46.568 --> 00:47.830
I'll see you later.
Be safe, yeah?

00:47.873 --> 00:49.440
- Yeah, you too.

00:49.484 --> 00:52.443
[indistinct chatter]

00:52.487 --> 00:59.494
♪

01:07.545 --> 01:09.417
[cheering]
- Damn!

01:11.549 --> 01:14.683
- Hey, who's got next?

01:14.726 --> 01:16.511
Come on.

01:16.554 --> 01:18.556
- I got next.

01:24.345 --> 01:26.651
- All right.
- All right.

01:30.699 --> 01:33.615
What, you're not impressed?

01:33.658 --> 01:35.182
- No.

01:35.225 --> 01:37.532
You think they could've
shot this better?

01:37.575 --> 01:41.144
All right, look,
anyone who lives here knows

01:41.188 --> 01:42.537
there is two Burnsides.

01:42.580 --> 01:45.496
- So you Burnside
born and raised?

01:45.540 --> 01:48.717
- No, I left Bronzeville
for here.

01:48.760 --> 01:51.546
- You left Bronzeville
for here?

01:51.589 --> 01:55.419
- [laughs]
- The Black metropolis?

01:55.463 --> 01:56.855
Okay.

01:56.899 --> 01:59.293
For here?
- For here.

02:01.817 --> 02:04.254
People make communities.

02:04.298 --> 02:06.604
- Let me ask you this.
- Hmm?

02:06.648 --> 02:11.305
- So how do two people
meet at a bar,

02:11.348 --> 02:12.741
talk for hours,

02:12.784 --> 02:16.919
and fail to learn
each other's names?

02:16.962 --> 02:18.877
- More fun that way.

02:18.921 --> 02:23.404
- Okay, stranger,

02:23.447 --> 02:26.320
you wanna dance?

02:26.363 --> 02:29.801
- Uh-huh. I do.

02:34.719 --> 02:36.199
[whispers]
Not here.

02:36.243 --> 02:43.250
♪

03:04.880 --> 03:07.491
- There she go.

03:07.535 --> 03:10.233
Hey.
- Hey, you.

03:13.628 --> 03:16.544
- Girl, talk to me.

03:16.587 --> 03:17.980
- We're getting personal
now, huh?

03:18.023 --> 03:20.722
- Yeah, we about this, baby.
- Mm-hmm.

03:20.765 --> 03:22.724
- Unless you wanna
remain nameless.

03:24.856 --> 03:27.816
- I'm Celeste.

03:27.859 --> 03:29.252
- Mm.

03:31.733 --> 03:32.734
Kev.

03:36.868 --> 03:38.043
- [sighs]

03:38.087 --> 03:39.523
- Hmm.

03:39.567 --> 03:41.743
Impressive art.
- Thanks.

03:45.007 --> 03:46.487
- You a artist?

03:48.967 --> 03:50.926
Or activist?

03:50.969 --> 03:54.321
- More like slacktivist.

03:54.364 --> 03:57.454
Just fighting the good fight
from my own little lane.

03:57.498 --> 03:59.413
That one's by one of my kids.

03:59.456 --> 04:02.764
Bit of Ernest Withers'
social realism

04:02.807 --> 04:04.896
at play there for sure.

04:04.940 --> 04:06.289
- Kids?

04:06.333 --> 04:07.812
- Oh, I teach art.

04:07.856 --> 04:08.987
- Okay.
- Mm.

04:09.031 --> 04:10.902
- [chuckles]
Okay.

04:10.946 --> 04:12.513
- You want coffee?

04:12.556 --> 04:16.430
I'm not making you breakfast,
but I will give you coffee.

04:16.473 --> 04:18.301
- Nah, I'm okay.

04:18.345 --> 04:20.999
I should probably start
getting ready for work.

04:21.043 --> 04:22.653
- What do you do?

04:22.697 --> 04:24.916
[soft suggestive music]

04:24.960 --> 04:27.528
Come on, it's your turn.

04:27.571 --> 04:30.879
- I just do boring work
for the city, that's all.

04:32.794 --> 04:34.056
- So what's up?

04:36.493 --> 04:37.886
Can I call you?

04:37.929 --> 04:39.801
- No.

04:41.455 --> 04:43.021
You should come find me again.

04:45.720 --> 04:47.287
Keep it interesting.

04:49.811 --> 04:52.814
[sirens wailing]

04:54.598 --> 04:57.079
- Whoa, hey, what's going on?

05:00.648 --> 05:03.607
[suspenseful music]

05:03.651 --> 05:04.956
♪

05:05.000 --> 05:06.436
- Getting additional
tickets over here.

05:06.480 --> 05:07.698
Let's get more cars
to the shots fired.

05:07.742 --> 05:08.873
94th and Ellis.

05:08.917 --> 05:11.093
- 50-21 David,
plain clothes responding.

05:15.619 --> 05:17.578
[screams and shouting]

05:17.621 --> 05:18.796
Hey, how many
offenders on scene?

05:18.840 --> 05:20.537
We still got offenders?
- Just rolled up.

05:23.453 --> 05:26.456
[car horn blaring]

05:32.810 --> 05:34.638
- Hey, we're gonna need
some paramedics over here.

05:34.682 --> 05:36.423
- It's en route.
- Okay.

05:37.859 --> 05:39.817
Hey.

05:39.861 --> 05:41.602
- [gasping]
- Hey.

05:41.645 --> 05:43.473
Hey, hey. You're okay.

05:43.517 --> 05:45.736
- You're okay, I'm a cop.
You gonna be all right.

05:45.780 --> 05:46.868
- Dad!

05:46.911 --> 05:49.827
Dad, please! Please, wake up!

05:49.871 --> 05:51.829
- Where are those paramedics?

05:51.873 --> 05:54.484
- I got this.
Get in there, come on.

05:54.528 --> 05:55.659
We got multiple GSW.

05:55.703 --> 05:57.008
He's already lost
a lot of blood.

05:57.052 --> 06:00.447
- Please, somebody help my dad!
He's bleeding!

06:00.490 --> 06:02.013
Please, he's been shot.
Help me!

06:02.057 --> 06:03.624
- I'm coming.
- Hey, where are you going?

06:03.667 --> 06:04.842
- He's gone, I'm sorry.

06:04.886 --> 06:06.714
He's already gone.

06:06.757 --> 06:13.416
♪

06:23.470 --> 06:24.688
- What happened?

06:24.732 --> 06:26.560
- It's all good.
What do we got?

06:26.603 --> 06:28.126
- Drive-by shooting, four vics

06:28.170 --> 06:29.867
and a pedestrian on
the other side of the line.

06:29.911 --> 06:31.216
A father was hit right here.

06:31.260 --> 06:33.088
His daughter was grazed
on the passenger side.

06:33.131 --> 06:35.133
Out-of-towners from Madison.
- Huh.

06:35.177 --> 06:36.483
- Decided to go through
the drive-through,

06:36.526 --> 06:38.572
he takes a GSW in the back.

06:38.615 --> 06:39.921
- Hey, the daughter
see anything?

06:39.964 --> 06:42.619
- Uh, yeah, she saw the car.

06:42.663 --> 06:44.534
It was a red SUV,
two offenders.

06:44.578 --> 06:45.927
Both were masked and hooded,

06:45.970 --> 06:48.103
and it was the passenger
who was dumping the shots.

06:48.146 --> 06:50.148
- Name of the victim
is Anthony Wiggins.

06:50.192 --> 06:52.586
- Yeah, he rolled with
the Burn City Hustlers.

06:52.629 --> 06:54.065
Did a 10-year stint
for drug trafficking,

06:54.109 --> 06:55.719
was released a month ago.

06:55.763 --> 06:58.853
- So based on the amount
of lead this guy took,

06:58.896 --> 07:00.811
trajectory of the bullets,

07:00.855 --> 07:02.117
we think Wiggins
was the target.

07:02.160 --> 07:05.076
All the rest of this
is just collateral damage.

07:05.120 --> 07:06.513
- We're waiting on the server

07:06.556 --> 07:07.862
for the footage
from the restaurant,

07:07.905 --> 07:09.907
but the place next door,
they got security cams

07:09.951 --> 07:12.083
and it's pretty clear
from the video.

07:12.127 --> 07:13.215
We can't see the shooting,

07:13.258 --> 07:14.259
but the whole block
had a good view.

07:14.303 --> 07:15.609
There was kids
sitting on a stoop

07:15.652 --> 07:17.001
when the shots went off.
- All right.

07:17.045 --> 07:18.699
So knock-and-talk
the hell out of them.

07:18.742 --> 07:21.266
Rest of us,
grid-search for the weapon.

07:21.310 --> 07:23.443
Dig into all gang disputes.

07:25.140 --> 07:27.664
- Let's go, Ru.
- Yeah.

07:30.928 --> 07:33.670
- See that?
- Yeah.

07:33.714 --> 07:36.717
- You left early.
I didn't even hear you leave.

07:36.760 --> 07:38.109
- I was trying
to let you sleep.

07:38.153 --> 07:40.982
We talked all night.
I just wanted to go to work.

07:45.682 --> 07:47.075
- Hey.

07:47.118 --> 07:48.946
Hey, hey, hey, hey, hey.
Slow down--

07:48.990 --> 07:51.079
- I'm not gonna talk to you.
- Hey!

07:51.122 --> 07:52.559
Man, you don't
have to talk to me,

07:52.602 --> 07:54.082
but the way you walking off
fast makes me feel like

07:54.125 --> 07:55.779
you know something, so did you
see that shooting or not?

07:55.823 --> 07:57.041
- I wasn't a witness.

07:57.085 --> 07:58.956
So go ahead and roll on out

07:59.000 --> 08:00.828
and claim it was another
gang on gang shooting.

08:00.871 --> 08:02.177
Go on, sellout.

08:02.220 --> 08:04.875
- "Sellout"?

08:04.919 --> 08:07.530
That's original.

08:07.574 --> 08:09.271
I'ma keep it moving.
We got everything we need.

08:09.314 --> 08:11.142
We know for a fact that
the dude that got shot

08:11.186 --> 08:12.709
was active with
the Burn City Hustlers.

08:12.753 --> 08:15.059
- Keyword, "was."

08:15.103 --> 08:16.583
- So you know
something I don't?

08:18.846 --> 08:21.805
Kid implies that Wiggins
was no longer in the game.

08:21.849 --> 08:24.155
Changed his life,
found God in the penitentiary.

08:24.199 --> 08:25.330
Confirmed that with Stateville.

08:25.374 --> 08:27.158
While inside,
Wiggins actually started

08:27.202 --> 08:28.551
a violence intervention
program.

08:28.595 --> 08:29.683
- Huh.

08:29.726 --> 08:32.555
- Two days ago,
confronts this man,

08:32.599 --> 08:34.731
Moe Hubbard,
street legend from the 90s.

08:34.775 --> 08:36.167
- Hubbard has never done time.

08:36.211 --> 08:37.647
He was arrested six times.

08:37.691 --> 08:39.649
Dealing, homicide,
nothing has ever stuck.

08:39.693 --> 08:41.042
Teflon.

08:41.085 --> 08:43.305
- So two days ago,
when Wiggins confronts Hubbard,

08:43.348 --> 08:44.654
somebody catches it
on Instagram.

08:44.698 --> 08:46.830
Watch this.

08:46.874 --> 08:47.875
- Wait.

08:47.918 --> 08:49.572
What you gotta say, baby?

08:49.616 --> 08:50.921
- You just a pariah, Hubbs.

08:50.965 --> 08:52.880
A weak pathetic thug
preying on young brothers.

08:52.923 --> 08:54.664
- See, you talk too much, man.

08:54.708 --> 08:56.013
Way too much.
- 48 hours later,

08:56.057 --> 08:58.059
Higgins was killed
in that drive-through.

08:58.102 --> 08:59.626
- All right,
we got anything concrete?

08:59.669 --> 09:00.844
Connect Hubbard
to the shooting?

09:00.888 --> 09:01.845
- No, of course not.

09:01.889 --> 09:03.151
No red SUV,

09:03.194 --> 09:04.848
no ballistics match,
but we're still digging.

09:04.892 --> 09:07.198
- Where's Hubbard now?

09:07.242 --> 09:09.200
- Got a recording studio
for young rappers.

09:09.244 --> 09:10.680
Acts like he's all about
the kids.

09:10.724 --> 09:12.595
Promises hope,
hands them guns instead.

09:12.639 --> 09:14.379
- Hmm, all right,
rest of you keep digging.

09:14.423 --> 09:18.209
Kev, let's you and me
pay Hubbard a visit.

09:18.253 --> 09:20.603
- ♪ Rappin' Miami,
flight just landed ♪

09:20.647 --> 09:22.692
♪ Six points, I'm catchin'
a beat like Randy ♪

09:22.736 --> 09:24.781
- Hmm. Okay.

09:24.825 --> 09:26.566
- Moe Hubbard.

09:28.829 --> 09:30.700
- [sighs]
[music stops]

09:32.093 --> 09:34.617
Ah.

09:34.661 --> 09:36.184
Y'all must be here
about that shooting.

09:36.227 --> 09:37.794
Hmm.

09:40.928 --> 09:43.931
How can I be of service?

09:43.974 --> 09:45.149
- So you knew Anthony Wiggins?

09:45.193 --> 09:47.848
- Violence interventionist?

09:47.891 --> 09:49.850
Yeah, my guy.

09:49.893 --> 09:52.679
- Yeah?
You guys don't look too chummy.

09:52.722 --> 09:54.419
- Way too much.
You know you talk....

09:54.463 --> 09:57.379
- Two days later, he was dead.

09:57.422 --> 09:59.686
You know anything about that?

09:59.729 --> 10:01.078
- Getting shot up?

10:01.122 --> 10:02.863
Nah, can't relate.

10:02.906 --> 10:05.126
[chuckles]

10:05.169 --> 10:07.171
I know if you
a violence interventionist

10:07.215 --> 10:08.825
and you get shot,

10:08.869 --> 10:11.698
you probably just got fired.

10:11.741 --> 10:14.744
[laughter]

10:14.788 --> 10:17.660
You know, intervention is
a dangerous line of work.

10:17.704 --> 10:19.923
- Oh, yeah.
- Mm-hmm.

10:19.967 --> 10:22.447
- Where were you this morning?

10:22.491 --> 10:24.014
- Man, here.

10:24.058 --> 10:26.234
Finishing up some songs.

10:26.277 --> 10:28.758
- I'm gonna need your security
footage from this morning.

10:28.802 --> 10:30.630
- Would be my pleasure.

10:36.461 --> 10:40.074
- Son of a bitch
basically told us he did it.

10:40.117 --> 10:42.380
- Well, there he is
at the time of the shooting.

10:42.424 --> 10:45.079
He could've outsourced the job.
- We got something.

10:45.122 --> 10:47.385
Restaurant footage
finally came in.

10:47.429 --> 10:50.911
Okay, so--yeah, here we go.

10:50.954 --> 10:52.956
Red SUV swerves into the lot.

10:53.000 --> 10:55.916
The passenger
fires at Wiggins' car

10:55.959 --> 10:59.789
and then, here we get 'em.
- Looks like kids.

10:59.833 --> 11:02.226
- You can't see faces, but you
can see the driver's hat,

11:02.270 --> 11:04.315
and you can just make out
the bottom of the logo.

11:04.359 --> 11:07.971
Now, we ran it through
every system we got

11:08.015 --> 11:10.757
and came back Chi-Teen Arts.

11:10.800 --> 11:13.368
- Privately run program
contracted by CPS.

11:13.411 --> 11:15.762
It's the only arts program
they use.

11:15.805 --> 11:17.720
At-risk teens,
they get referred

11:17.764 --> 11:19.069
by their teachers, counsellors.

11:19.113 --> 11:20.331
- Who runs it?

11:20.375 --> 11:23.160
- Woman by the name
of Celeste Nichols.

11:23.204 --> 11:24.988
She lives in Burnside.

11:25.032 --> 11:27.991
[tense music]

11:28.035 --> 11:30.733
♪

11:30.777 --> 11:32.213
- Well, let's hope
this Miss Nichols

11:32.256 --> 11:34.911
can help us ID at least
one of the offenders.

11:34.955 --> 11:35.956
Hit it.

11:35.999 --> 11:37.348
- Kev, you and me? Yeah?

11:39.350 --> 11:41.222
- Yo, Ru.

11:41.265 --> 11:43.746
- Yeah?
- Um...

11:43.790 --> 11:45.356
[clicks tongue]

11:45.400 --> 11:47.271
I need you
to take this one for me.

11:47.315 --> 11:49.273
- Why? What's going on?

11:51.014 --> 11:53.843
- Last night at the Pennyhole,

11:53.887 --> 11:56.367
I met her, Celeste.

11:57.499 --> 11:58.935
I know her.

11:58.979 --> 12:00.807
- Oh.

12:00.850 --> 12:02.286
- And she does not know
I'm a cop.

12:02.330 --> 12:03.505
- I'll go talk to her.

12:03.548 --> 12:05.333
Get some names,
be in and out, real easy.

12:05.376 --> 12:08.075
I got you, man.
- My man.

12:08.118 --> 12:15.125
♪

12:21.610 --> 12:21.958
.

12:22.002 --> 12:23.960
- Celeste Nichols? Chicago PD.

12:24.004 --> 12:26.658
- Full disclosure,
any truancy or juvie issues

12:26.702 --> 12:28.095
must go through CPS.

12:28.138 --> 12:30.445
I don't give information
on my kids.

12:30.488 --> 12:32.969
This is their safe space.

12:33.013 --> 12:34.101
- Yeah.

12:36.059 --> 12:39.541
Wow. These are powerful images.

12:39.584 --> 12:41.456
The kids are really good.

12:41.499 --> 12:43.110
- "Tale of Two Cities"
kind of thing.

12:43.153 --> 12:44.154
- Okay.

12:44.198 --> 12:45.547
- Way the kids
see themselves...

12:45.590 --> 12:47.027
- Yeah.

12:47.070 --> 12:48.985
- Way the rest
of the world sees 'em.

12:49.029 --> 12:51.422
- Yeah, I like that.

12:51.466 --> 12:55.296
Celeste, we think two of
your students are in trouble.

12:55.339 --> 12:58.038
- CPD's in my class,
I'd say so too.

12:58.081 --> 13:00.127
- Ms. Nichols,

13:00.170 --> 13:02.999
do you recognize either
of the boys in these images?

13:05.828 --> 13:08.788
[suspenseful music]

13:08.831 --> 13:12.835
♪

13:12.879 --> 13:14.184
Yes?

13:15.751 --> 13:17.666
- It's--

13:17.709 --> 13:20.103
I mean, it's not
very good quality.

13:20.147 --> 13:23.150
- Well, you can see
the Chi-Teen Arts logo.

13:23.193 --> 13:26.327
And we think one or maybe
both of them are students here.

13:26.370 --> 13:28.068
Take a look again.

13:28.111 --> 13:29.591
- They're covered up.

13:29.634 --> 13:31.245
It's grainy.

13:31.288 --> 13:33.377
- Yeah, but Celeste,
it feels like you can tell.

13:35.858 --> 13:38.513
- Could be anyone.
- That makes things difficult.

13:38.556 --> 13:40.123
That means we're gonna
have to come down here,

13:40.167 --> 13:42.647
and we're gonna have to talk
to all 175 of your students,

13:42.691 --> 13:45.085
possibly have to put them down
as persons of interest.

13:45.128 --> 13:46.521
Ms. Nichols,

13:46.564 --> 13:48.871
we're gonna have to
put them on the record, so--

13:48.915 --> 13:50.655
- Yeah? Is that right?

13:50.699 --> 13:52.570
- Yeah, it is.

13:52.614 --> 13:54.137
Or you can come down
to the station,

13:54.181 --> 13:56.792
and you can talk to us.

13:56.836 --> 14:03.843
♪

14:04.931 --> 14:06.541
- Like I told the first
two officers,

14:06.584 --> 14:10.719
it's very hard to recognize
who that is.

14:10.762 --> 14:13.243
- The concern in your voice
says otherwise.

14:13.287 --> 14:14.592
You came here because

14:14.636 --> 14:16.072
you clearly care about
the kids in this photo.

14:16.116 --> 14:19.380
- That's a presumptive opinion,
at best.

14:19.423 --> 14:21.121
- At worst, the truth?

14:21.164 --> 14:23.514
- I'm here
because your cop friend

14:23.558 --> 14:25.212
threatened the safety
of the kids in my class.

14:25.255 --> 14:27.301
He knew exactly
why I wouldn't want them

14:27.344 --> 14:31.261
put in your system,
in your gang database,

14:31.305 --> 14:32.567
and so he used
that to get me here

14:32.610 --> 14:35.657
and put me in a cold
interrogation room

14:35.700 --> 14:38.529
to make me feel as if
I've done something wrong.

14:38.573 --> 14:40.705
- Smart.
- Mm.

14:40.749 --> 14:42.403
- Okay.

14:42.446 --> 14:43.839
Kids in that photo

14:43.883 --> 14:45.493
shot four people.

14:45.536 --> 14:49.801
This guy died
en route to Chicago Med.

14:49.845 --> 14:53.414
Victim by the name
of Anthony Wiggins,

14:53.457 --> 14:55.198
he died on scene.

14:55.242 --> 14:57.722
So that's why my cop friend
brought you here.

14:57.766 --> 14:59.376
Yes or no,

14:59.420 --> 15:01.161
do you know who they are?

15:01.204 --> 15:08.211
♪

15:09.909 --> 15:12.781
- No. No, I don't.

15:12.824 --> 15:15.610
I have 175 kids in my program,

15:15.653 --> 15:20.441
and this photo doesn't
show me enough to ID them.

15:20.484 --> 15:22.791
But I do have
another class to prep for,

15:22.834 --> 15:24.706
and I know my rights.

15:24.749 --> 15:27.317
I'd like to leave now.

15:36.413 --> 15:39.286
- So you're actually
kind of into this lady?

15:39.329 --> 15:41.549
- Come on, man.

15:41.592 --> 15:43.899
- How'd you avoid
telling her you're CPD?

15:43.943 --> 15:46.249
- Just felt kind of good to be
the dude she met at the bar

15:46.293 --> 15:48.730
and not the Black cop.
- Mm.

15:48.773 --> 15:50.036
- Didn't have
to defend the badge,

15:50.079 --> 15:51.863
didn't have to prove
my Blackness, that's it.

15:51.907 --> 15:53.865
Hey, she's moving,
she's moving, she's moving.

16:00.742 --> 16:03.658
- Hey, I need you to call me,
okay?

16:03.701 --> 16:05.312
I don't care
what the cops are saying,

16:05.355 --> 16:08.402
but I need to hear it from you,
okay, so call me.

16:08.445 --> 16:13.450
♪

16:13.494 --> 16:15.365
- Sure seemed like
whoever she was calling

16:15.409 --> 16:17.019
was our offender.

16:17.063 --> 16:18.760
I could bring her back in.

16:18.803 --> 16:20.805
- I doubt that'll
get her talking.

16:20.849 --> 16:22.894
Probably just make her angrier.

16:22.938 --> 16:24.679
- She wasn't angry.

16:24.722 --> 16:26.768
- We could put
a warrant on her phone.

16:26.811 --> 16:29.249
- Look, there's no way the DA
is gonna sign off on that.

16:29.292 --> 16:31.816
Look, we need more.
- Hey.

16:31.860 --> 16:34.210
Okay, so I ran
Celeste's social media.

16:34.254 --> 16:35.907
She seems close
with most of her kids,

16:35.951 --> 16:38.693
and she's right,
it is their safe space.

16:38.736 --> 16:40.477
But 73 of her male students
were in CPS

16:40.521 --> 16:41.522
at the time of the shooting.

16:41.565 --> 16:43.306
So I ran the remaining 27.

16:43.350 --> 16:47.397
Of those, these four stood out.

16:48.746 --> 16:51.967
Sarge, she spends extra time
with these four.

16:52.011 --> 16:55.362
She takes them on field trips
and books them art shows.

16:55.405 --> 16:56.537
They've each had
a rough upbringing,

16:56.580 --> 16:57.755
lots of juggling with family.

16:57.799 --> 16:59.322
They're all into art and music,

16:59.366 --> 17:01.455
so they could've crossed paths
with Hubbard, so--

17:01.498 --> 17:05.067
- Well, we still need more.

17:05.111 --> 17:06.503
A lot more.

17:06.547 --> 17:07.983
- Okay.

17:09.332 --> 17:10.464
- I know her.

17:13.510 --> 17:15.643
Celeste.

17:15.686 --> 17:17.471
I met her at a bar.

17:17.514 --> 17:19.995
- Didn't feel like sharing?

17:20.039 --> 17:22.737
- I didn't think
it would matter.

17:22.780 --> 17:25.392
But she does not know
I'm a cop.

17:25.435 --> 17:27.437
- Huh.
- So I work her.

17:27.481 --> 17:28.656
I get a number
off the cell phone

17:28.699 --> 17:30.005
and I confirm the name.

17:30.049 --> 17:31.398
- Well, that's a good idea.

17:31.441 --> 17:32.921
You do that.

17:32.964 --> 17:36.620
♪

17:46.065 --> 17:46.239
.

17:46.282 --> 17:48.806
[knocking on door]

17:48.850 --> 17:50.069
[door clicks open]

17:51.809 --> 17:53.159
- Hey.

17:53.202 --> 17:55.204
You know, you never
gave me your number.

17:55.248 --> 17:58.251
So I figured I'd find you.

17:58.294 --> 18:00.818
- See, pure romance.

18:00.862 --> 18:01.863
- Hmm.

18:04.257 --> 18:06.694
You okay? This a bad time?

18:06.737 --> 18:07.912
- Bad day.

18:07.956 --> 18:10.611
- Yeah, I understand.

18:10.654 --> 18:13.004
Well, you know, if you're gonna
feel better all by yourself,

18:13.048 --> 18:15.137
it probably
would've happened by now.

18:16.965 --> 18:18.662
- Come on, come on.

18:22.275 --> 18:25.104
- Okay, so this,
this isn't working at all.

18:25.147 --> 18:26.279
- What?

18:26.322 --> 18:27.758
- I was supposed to be
cheering you up.

18:27.802 --> 18:29.760
- I'm good.

18:29.804 --> 18:31.284
- Mm?

18:31.327 --> 18:32.763
- Yeah, I'm good.
I'm fine.

18:32.807 --> 18:34.287
- You playing it off well,
but I can tell

18:34.330 --> 18:37.986
you ain't really--
ain't really listening.

18:38.029 --> 18:40.858
- My job is sometimes
harder than--

18:40.902 --> 18:43.122
- Kids, they just
pains in the ass?

18:43.165 --> 18:45.341
- No, no, they're just--

18:47.213 --> 18:49.345
They're just kids.

18:52.305 --> 18:55.960
Not allowed to be
for very long, you know?

18:56.004 --> 18:57.745
- How is that?

18:59.442 --> 19:02.793
- How is it not?

19:02.837 --> 19:06.406
They got Burnside,
Garfield Park,

19:06.449 --> 19:09.713
Anglewood all telling 'em,

19:09.757 --> 19:11.193
"Don't get caught lacking.

19:11.237 --> 19:12.716
"Keep your gun,

19:12.760 --> 19:16.198
keep eyes in the back of
your head or lose your head."

19:16.242 --> 19:18.766
You know, they got the police,
they got TV,

19:18.809 --> 19:21.682
hell, they got social media

19:21.725 --> 19:26.426
all showing them
the angry Black woman,

19:26.469 --> 19:27.775
the scary Black man,

19:27.818 --> 19:29.777
a Black kid

19:29.820 --> 19:32.040
shooting another Black kid.

19:33.868 --> 19:35.783
"So be ready.

19:35.826 --> 19:38.351
Be running,
be afraid of your own."

19:38.394 --> 19:41.919
[solemn music]

19:41.963 --> 19:44.226
I'm sorry.

19:44.270 --> 19:45.967
I'm ranting. Let's--

19:46.010 --> 19:47.838
- No.
- Talk you.

19:47.882 --> 19:49.188
- No, you're
not ranting at all.

19:49.231 --> 19:50.711
It's okay.

19:50.754 --> 19:53.235
I got a little brother
and a little sister.

19:53.279 --> 19:55.324
- Yeah?

19:55.368 --> 19:57.196
- I raised them,

19:57.239 --> 19:59.285
so I get it.

19:59.328 --> 20:01.722
Most of the time,
it does feel like it's us

20:01.765 --> 20:04.115
versus whatever world
the white man forced on us

20:04.159 --> 20:05.465
or us versus--
- Against the world that

20:05.508 --> 20:08.859
we had to force on ourselves.
- On ourselves.

20:08.903 --> 20:10.252
Right.

20:10.296 --> 20:12.907
- I swear,

20:12.950 --> 20:17.912
people never get
how hard it hurts

20:17.955 --> 20:22.046
to not have a place

20:22.090 --> 20:23.874
to feel seen.

20:23.918 --> 20:30.925
♪

20:31.795 --> 20:34.798
[both moaning]

20:36.583 --> 20:38.846
- You know, I can probably
use another girl beer.

20:38.889 --> 20:40.108
- [chuckles]

20:40.151 --> 20:42.806
- Before we go there.
- Yeah.

20:42.850 --> 20:44.112
- I'ma get you one.

20:44.155 --> 20:46.245
You stay right there. Hold on.

20:52.338 --> 20:55.297
[vocalizing]

21:01.869 --> 21:06.308
[phone ringing]

21:06.352 --> 21:08.571
- [sighs]

21:08.615 --> 21:11.792
Hey, are you all right?

21:11.835 --> 21:13.489
Hey, okay, no, no, no, no.
Slow down, slow down.

21:13.533 --> 21:15.404
What happened?

21:15.448 --> 21:18.929
I get that,
but this is not the solution.

21:18.973 --> 21:22.150
Okay, I'm on my way right now.

21:22.193 --> 21:25.545
- What's going on?
- I, um, I just gotta--

21:25.588 --> 21:27.547
I got something
to take care of.

21:27.590 --> 21:29.462
- Is that one of your students?
'Cause I can help.

21:29.505 --> 21:31.072
- No, I don't need any help.

21:31.115 --> 21:33.248
- Is this kid okay?

21:33.292 --> 21:35.337
- No. No, I don't think so.

21:35.381 --> 21:37.818
I don't know what I'm gonna do,
but I gotta do something.

21:37.861 --> 21:39.428
- Yeah, well,
let me come with you.

21:39.472 --> 21:40.864
I know you don't
know me that well,

21:40.908 --> 21:43.867
but I'm guessing from
everything you just told me,

21:43.911 --> 21:45.304
whoever this kid is,

21:45.347 --> 21:48.959
I promise you, I can help.

21:49.003 --> 21:51.048
- [exhales]
Okay.

21:51.092 --> 21:53.050
Okay, come on.

21:53.094 --> 21:54.965
[suspenseful music]

21:55.009 --> 21:57.011
- So who's this kid?

21:57.054 --> 21:58.882
- Lewis.

21:58.926 --> 22:00.623
Lewis Dotson.

22:00.667 --> 22:02.016
He's sweet.

22:02.059 --> 22:04.148
He's been a student of mine
for two years.

22:04.192 --> 22:07.238
Oh, turn right, right here.

22:09.545 --> 22:11.373
- Place looks abandoned.
- It is.

22:11.417 --> 22:13.332
He said he's in the back unit.

22:15.334 --> 22:17.205
- Lewis Dotson, 15.

22:17.248 --> 22:19.468
He's one of the four we ID'd,
no priors.

22:19.512 --> 22:21.035
Not a lot of truancies.

22:21.078 --> 22:22.079
Good kid.

22:26.562 --> 22:28.434
- Okay, everybody
is in position?

22:28.477 --> 22:31.393
Just stay steady.
Let Atwater get him talking.

22:31.437 --> 22:33.613
Wait for my signal.

22:33.656 --> 22:40.533
♪

22:42.230 --> 22:44.188
- You're okay.

22:44.232 --> 22:46.277
- No, uh-uh--
- Look, he's Kevin, okay?

22:46.321 --> 22:47.409
- No, no.
- A friend.

22:47.453 --> 22:48.367
- I don't know this guy,
Ms. Nichols.

22:48.410 --> 22:49.585
- He's gonna help.
- No.

22:49.629 --> 22:51.282
- Hey, Celeste, I can step out.

22:51.326 --> 22:52.545
It's okay.
- No, no.

22:52.588 --> 22:54.024
Lewis, I wouldn't have
brought him here

22:54.068 --> 22:57.071
if I didn't trust him, okay?
He said he'd help.

22:57.114 --> 22:58.942
Lewis, what happened?

22:58.986 --> 23:00.683
- Look, I was just driving.

23:00.727 --> 23:02.381
- So it was you in that photo.

23:02.424 --> 23:03.382
- The cops got a photo?

23:03.425 --> 23:04.687
- Damn, Lewis,

23:04.731 --> 23:06.515
you didn't know
where you were driving?

23:10.171 --> 23:11.651
- Did you know?

23:17.308 --> 23:19.310
[gasps shakily]

23:21.095 --> 23:23.227
How the hell do I help him?

23:25.752 --> 23:28.276
- [whispering]
It's okay.

23:34.282 --> 23:36.240
Okay, all right, Lew--

23:40.157 --> 23:43.465
- What happened?
We lose his signal?

23:43.509 --> 23:45.989
- Yeah, I don't know
what happened, boss.

23:46.033 --> 23:48.165
Signal's completely down.
I got nothing.

23:48.209 --> 23:50.254
- Did you touch the gun?

23:52.605 --> 23:54.041
Answer me.

23:54.084 --> 23:55.216
Come on, man.

23:55.259 --> 23:57.087
- Just to dump it.

23:57.131 --> 24:00.351
I threw it in the river.

24:00.395 --> 24:01.744
- All right, okay,
what about the person

24:01.788 --> 24:03.485
that you were with, all right?

24:03.529 --> 24:06.575
Why did he shoot these men?
Who are they to you?

24:08.490 --> 24:09.709
- They were Hubbs' guys okay?

24:09.752 --> 24:13.060
- Hubb--Hubbard?
- Hubb, yes.

24:13.103 --> 24:15.628
He was gonna
kill me if I didn't.

24:15.671 --> 24:17.107
- Chicago PD.
- [screams]

24:17.151 --> 24:18.500
- Let me see your hands.
- Get down, Lewis!

24:18.544 --> 24:20.110
- Keep your hands
where I can see 'em.

24:20.154 --> 24:21.764
- Lewis, get down!
- Let me see your hands.

24:21.808 --> 24:23.505
- Do it. Go on the floor.

24:23.549 --> 24:25.246
- Lewis.
- Turn around.

24:25.289 --> 24:26.421
Get your hands
behind your back.

24:26.465 --> 24:27.596
Get on the floor.

24:27.640 --> 24:28.771
- Keep your hands
where I can see them.

24:28.815 --> 24:30.512
You got me?
- Bell on the ground.

24:33.341 --> 24:35.343
- I'm sorry.

24:41.480 --> 24:41.654
.

24:41.697 --> 24:44.570
[suspenseful music]

24:44.613 --> 24:49.444
♪

24:49.488 --> 24:51.751
- You gotta get him
a good lawyer.

24:51.794 --> 24:53.709
- He's a minor.
He's entitled to a lawyer.

24:53.753 --> 24:54.754
- Yeah, it doesn't mean
he's gonna know

24:54.797 --> 24:57.974
how to get a decent one.
- Okay.

24:58.018 --> 24:59.454
- I'm sorry.

24:59.498 --> 25:01.717
I'm sorry I got you
in this, Kevin.

25:01.761 --> 25:03.763
- Come on, let's go.

25:05.591 --> 25:07.941
We'll search you upstairs.
Come on.

25:07.984 --> 25:14.991
♪

25:24.479 --> 25:25.915
- I was just about
to bring him up to you.

25:25.959 --> 25:28.614
- It's all good, I got him.

25:28.657 --> 25:30.616
Come on.

25:30.659 --> 25:32.661
Let's go.

25:35.708 --> 25:36.752
- You're a cop.

25:36.796 --> 25:38.449
Ms. Nichols is gonna hate you.

25:38.493 --> 25:41.583
I'll tell her as soon as I can
you're a damn traitor!

25:41.627 --> 25:44.368
- My Black ass not being here,

25:44.412 --> 25:45.892
picture that.

25:45.935 --> 25:48.590
I'm the best thing
you got going right now.

25:48.634 --> 25:51.071
So listen to me.

25:51.114 --> 25:53.769
When I take you
into that interview room,

25:53.813 --> 25:55.031
I'm gonna read you your rights,

25:55.075 --> 25:57.556
and you're gonna
request a lawyer.

25:57.599 --> 26:00.994
Don't say anything else to me
but "lawyer."

26:02.517 --> 26:04.475
When you have your lawyer,

26:04.519 --> 26:07.130
when I ask you if you knew
where you were driving,

26:07.174 --> 26:08.654
tell me exactly
what you told me

26:08.697 --> 26:10.960
in that apartment complex.

26:11.004 --> 26:12.832
No, you did not.

26:15.661 --> 26:18.098
Whether you had
knowledge of the crime

26:18.141 --> 26:19.360
is gonna be
the difference between

26:19.403 --> 26:21.057
you living your life

26:21.101 --> 26:23.582
or giving it up
in a penitentiary.

26:24.844 --> 26:28.064
- Why--why are you doing this?

26:28.108 --> 26:31.720
- Ms. Nichols knows
who you really are.

26:31.764 --> 26:33.983
I believe her.

26:34.027 --> 26:36.072
I see it.

26:36.116 --> 26:39.902
I see you, okay?

26:39.946 --> 26:41.382
I see you.

26:43.427 --> 26:44.559
Come on.

26:47.170 --> 26:49.912
- I'm not following, Lewis.

26:49.956 --> 26:51.522
You didn't know
where you were driving,

26:51.566 --> 26:53.046
you had no idea
your friend had that gun?

26:53.089 --> 26:55.744
- Don't answer that.

26:55.788 --> 26:58.051
- So you just pulled
into that drive-through,

26:58.094 --> 26:59.574
your buddy next to you
starts shooting,

26:59.618 --> 27:03.665
but you had no knowledge
of his intention to do so?

27:03.709 --> 27:05.014
- No.

27:08.801 --> 27:10.672
- All right, well, Lewis,

27:10.716 --> 27:12.631
I need more than that.

27:12.674 --> 27:15.024
I need to know the name
of your friend.

27:15.068 --> 27:17.853
- My client
won't be providing that.

27:17.897 --> 27:24.904
♪

27:29.604 --> 27:31.127
- Nah, I wanna answer.

27:31.171 --> 27:32.476
- You don't have
to say anything.

27:32.520 --> 27:34.478
- No, I--

27:39.222 --> 27:43.139
It was my friend, Eric Boyle.

27:43.183 --> 27:45.881
- Eric Boyle, okay.

27:45.925 --> 27:47.491
- But--but look, I--

27:47.535 --> 27:48.928
I know he only
would've pulled that gun

27:48.971 --> 27:51.626
'cause Moe Hubbard
forced him to.

27:51.670 --> 27:53.062
Hubb--Hubbard, he owns him.

27:53.106 --> 27:55.717
He threatened to kill him.

27:55.761 --> 28:00.200
Moe, he gave Eric that weapon.

28:00.243 --> 28:03.116
Eric fired it
'cause he must've thought

28:03.159 --> 28:05.161
he didn't have a choice.

28:12.865 --> 28:14.170
- I think we got enough
to move on Hubbard.

28:14.214 --> 28:16.738
Definitely Eric Boyle.
- Okay, good.

28:16.782 --> 28:18.827
Well, patrol just confirmed
they're both

28:18.871 --> 28:20.611
at Drill Hubb Records
right now.

28:20.655 --> 28:23.832
So get arrest warrants.

28:23.876 --> 28:26.182
I'll get the marine unit,
start looking for that gun.

28:26.226 --> 28:28.924
- Copy that.

28:28.968 --> 28:30.665
- Hold up a sec, Kev.

28:31.971 --> 28:34.103
Oh.

28:34.147 --> 28:37.150
Kid gave just enough
to get Eric and Hubbard.

28:37.193 --> 28:38.847
- Got lucky.

28:38.891 --> 28:41.197
- What happened with your COH?

28:41.241 --> 28:43.156
- I don't know.
I need to check that battery.

28:45.680 --> 28:49.075
We good to move
on Hubbard and Eric?

28:49.118 --> 28:51.294
- Mm-hmm.

28:51.338 --> 28:52.731
- Okay.

28:58.824 --> 29:01.783
- Chicago PD, open up!

29:01.827 --> 29:03.176
- CPD, don't you move!

29:03.219 --> 29:04.307
- Let's see those hands, now!

29:04.351 --> 29:06.309
Do not move.
- Stay right there.

29:06.353 --> 29:09.008
You got anything on you?
- A gun.

29:11.706 --> 29:13.664
- Chicago PD, hands up.

29:13.708 --> 29:15.928
Uh-huh. Uh-huh, get up.

29:15.971 --> 29:18.234
Come on, get over there.

29:18.278 --> 29:20.193
- Take it y'all got a warrant?

29:23.718 --> 29:24.806
- Get up.

29:24.850 --> 29:31.857
♪

29:33.206 --> 29:34.947
- So just to confirm with you,

29:34.990 --> 29:38.689
your report says that
while the COH was out,

29:38.733 --> 29:40.822
Lewis told you he didn't
have knowledge of the crime

29:40.866 --> 29:42.693
about to be committed?
- Right.

29:42.737 --> 29:45.740
He told me a version of that
in the interview room.

29:45.784 --> 29:47.089
Why?

29:47.133 --> 29:50.353
- I'm just confirming
that he lied repeatedly.

29:50.397 --> 29:52.094
- How's that?

29:52.138 --> 29:54.618
- My investigators
found messaging

29:54.662 --> 29:57.621
between him and Eric Boyle.

29:57.665 --> 29:59.319
It sounded like Lewis
knew exactly

29:59.362 --> 30:01.016
where he was driving and why.

30:01.060 --> 30:03.236
- Well, that doesn't
prove anything.

30:03.279 --> 30:05.020
- He lied to you.

30:05.064 --> 30:07.196
He had knowledge of the crime.

30:07.240 --> 30:08.589
We'll be charging him
as an adult.

30:08.632 --> 30:10.983
- As an adult?

30:11.026 --> 30:13.202
A 15-year-old boy as an adult?

30:13.246 --> 30:14.638
- It's a double homicide.

30:14.682 --> 30:16.771
- Hey, he's also a kid
that got manipulated

30:16.815 --> 30:18.642
and threatened
by a grown-ass man.

30:18.686 --> 30:20.209
- And he committed a crime

30:20.253 --> 30:22.037
in which two men were killed.

30:22.081 --> 30:24.866
- Under the "do or die"
orders of a thug.

30:24.910 --> 30:27.390
That's not in the notes?

30:27.434 --> 30:28.870
Because right now,
it sounds like

30:28.914 --> 30:31.742
we're trying to create
a false narrative about a kid

30:31.786 --> 30:33.962
so that we can build a case.
- Kev.

30:34.006 --> 30:35.007
- No.

30:36.922 --> 30:38.706
I'm following evidence.

30:38.749 --> 30:40.751
I'm doing my job,
that's what I'm doing.

30:40.795 --> 30:44.625
And you have zero proof
he didn't have knowledge.

30:44.668 --> 30:46.627
- Wow.

30:48.020 --> 30:50.761
- Is there something else
you wanna say to me?

30:50.805 --> 30:51.806
Call me?

30:51.850 --> 30:53.112
I'm pretty sure every insult

30:53.155 --> 30:55.027
running through
your head right now,

30:55.070 --> 30:57.638
you've had thrown at yourself
100 times.

30:57.681 --> 31:00.641
[tense music]

31:00.684 --> 31:06.952
♪

31:06.995 --> 31:08.997
- If Lewis is gonna be
arraigned as an adult,

31:09.041 --> 31:10.869
we're gonna have
to transfer him to County.

31:10.912 --> 31:13.697
I'll get a transport car.
- Mm-mm.

31:15.786 --> 31:18.833
I'll transport him myself.

31:39.419 --> 31:41.682
- Look, man, I can't do this.
Please, man!

31:43.858 --> 31:45.120
Please.

31:45.164 --> 31:46.426
I didn't--
there's gotta be something--

31:46.469 --> 31:47.818
- Hey, hey, look at me.

31:47.862 --> 31:48.819
- There's gotta be
something, man.

31:48.863 --> 31:50.734
- Hey, look at me.
Look at me.

31:50.778 --> 31:51.953
You're gonna go in there,

31:51.997 --> 31:53.172
you're gonna
keep your head down,

31:53.215 --> 31:55.261
and you're gonna
hold yourself together,

31:55.304 --> 31:57.002
all right?

31:57.045 --> 31:59.265
You're gonna be fine.

31:59.308 --> 32:00.701
Believe that.

32:04.879 --> 32:07.751
- Look, man,
I lied to you, all right?

32:07.795 --> 32:10.363
I said I dumped the gun,
but I didn't.

32:10.406 --> 32:11.973
I got scared.

32:13.496 --> 32:14.758
[gunshots]

32:14.802 --> 32:16.325
[groans]

32:16.369 --> 32:19.328
[intense music]

32:19.372 --> 32:25.726
♪

32:25.769 --> 32:28.033
- Call it in, call it in!

32:28.076 --> 32:29.512
- K1, K1, shots fired.

32:29.556 --> 32:31.079
- Eric, stop!

32:46.051 --> 32:48.314
Don't fight me.
Do not fight me!

32:48.357 --> 32:49.968
Stop.

32:50.011 --> 32:54.973
Stop, stop, stop!

32:55.016 --> 32:56.931
Hubbard sent you, hmm?

32:56.975 --> 32:59.194
Tell me, talk to me!

32:59.238 --> 33:03.372
Was it worth it, huh?

33:03.416 --> 33:05.461
You don't even know
who you are yet.

33:05.505 --> 33:06.462
Why?

33:06.506 --> 33:09.030
- I got him.
- Huh, why?

33:09.074 --> 33:12.033
[somber music]

33:12.077 --> 33:18.997
♪

33:21.912 --> 33:23.088
[shouts]

33:38.929 --> 33:39.060
.

33:39.104 --> 33:40.844
- If you're coming down here
to give me a lecture--

33:40.888 --> 33:43.238
- I'm not.

33:43.282 --> 33:45.980
This wasn't on you.

33:46.024 --> 33:48.504
It isn't.

33:48.548 --> 33:51.986
I get why you did
what you did today.

33:52.030 --> 33:55.381
I also get that

33:55.424 --> 33:58.166
sometimes this job
chews up your soul

33:58.210 --> 34:01.169
in a different way
than it does mine.

34:04.433 --> 34:06.131
I respect the hell out of you

34:06.174 --> 34:08.263
that you stay here
when it does.

34:13.094 --> 34:15.357
- Is Eric talking?

34:15.401 --> 34:16.402
- No.

34:16.445 --> 34:19.187
- Hubbard?

34:19.231 --> 34:22.277
So we have no proof that
Hubbard sent him down there?

34:22.321 --> 34:24.192
- Not yet.

34:24.236 --> 34:25.411
- [exhales]

34:28.066 --> 34:30.416
Lewis was just about to tell me
what happened with the gun.

34:30.459 --> 34:31.808
He didn't dump it.

34:31.852 --> 34:33.114
- He didn't tell you
what he did with it?

34:33.158 --> 34:34.333
- It could be anywhere.

34:34.376 --> 34:35.899
- Hmm.

34:35.943 --> 34:37.814
- I just don't know where
he went after the shooting.

34:37.858 --> 34:39.120
I don't know.

34:45.083 --> 34:46.171
Hmm.

34:50.088 --> 34:52.177
I do know.

34:52.220 --> 34:53.308
Celeste said
he would go somewhere

34:53.352 --> 34:55.223
where he knew it was safe.

34:55.267 --> 34:58.096
[suspenseful music]

34:58.139 --> 35:04.102
♪

35:20.944 --> 35:22.120
Got it.

35:38.614 --> 35:42.270
That's the gun used in
the drive-through shooting.

35:42.314 --> 35:44.968
- Doesn't ring a bell?

35:45.012 --> 35:46.274
Huh.

35:46.318 --> 35:48.494
See, it turns out somebody put

35:48.537 --> 35:50.974
a Glock converter switch
on that weapon,

35:51.018 --> 35:54.108
made it fully automatic.

35:54.152 --> 35:57.198
Still nothing? Hmm.

35:57.242 --> 35:59.461
- Lewis is gone,
so he can't testify on that,

35:59.505 --> 36:02.464
but Eric Boyle is still here.

36:02.508 --> 36:04.162
Yeah, the police
didn't shoot him.

36:04.205 --> 36:07.165
Like I'm guessing
you thought they would.

36:07.208 --> 36:08.209
And he's talking.

36:08.253 --> 36:11.038
- Oh, he's talking.

36:11.081 --> 36:14.911
He's saying you gave him
the gun and the car.

36:14.955 --> 36:17.479
That you told him and Lewis
to shoot and kill Wiggins

36:17.523 --> 36:19.394
or you would shoot
and kill them.

36:19.438 --> 36:25.008
- If you think I'ma slip
for a confession,

36:25.052 --> 36:26.358
it ain't gone happen.

36:26.401 --> 36:28.969
- See, it turns out
we don't need it.

36:30.971 --> 36:33.365
Yeah, I'll be
seeing you around, Hubby.

36:35.236 --> 36:37.238
Why don't you fill him in, Kev?

36:37.282 --> 36:43.940
♪

36:44.593 --> 36:47.379
- See,

36:47.422 --> 36:52.035
shooters wear masks,
they wear gloves,

36:52.079 --> 36:53.211
they avoid the cameras,

36:53.254 --> 36:55.038
but for some reason,

36:55.082 --> 36:56.997
bangers always forget that

36:57.040 --> 36:59.434
when you load bullets
into a magazine,

36:59.478 --> 37:01.480
and when you put
a switch on a Glock

37:01.523 --> 37:03.525
and turn it into a mini AK-47,

37:03.569 --> 37:06.136
you leave partial prints.

37:08.313 --> 37:10.619
Your prints are on
both of those guns.

37:13.231 --> 37:16.277
That plus what we got
from Eric Boyle,

37:16.321 --> 37:18.236
you're done.

37:20.760 --> 37:21.935
So...

37:23.632 --> 37:27.070
Good luck at Stateville.

37:27.114 --> 37:28.202
Those "Free Hubbard" shirts
are gonna be

37:28.246 --> 37:30.073
pretty popular, though.

37:30.117 --> 37:37.124
♪

37:51.617 --> 37:54.228
- Did you hear what happened?

37:54.272 --> 37:56.012
- I wish I could've
been here sooner.

37:57.536 --> 37:59.146
- Come on.

38:04.630 --> 38:08.155
You know they were gonna
charge Lewis as an adult.

38:08.198 --> 38:09.591
I can't even understand that.

38:09.635 --> 38:12.420
He's 15.

38:12.464 --> 38:15.075
And we both know

38:15.118 --> 38:17.643
if Lewis was a white kid,

38:17.686 --> 38:19.558
they'd paint a picture
of a helpless victim

38:19.601 --> 38:22.343
bullied into crime.

38:22.387 --> 38:25.085
I mean, he didn't even
have his hand on the trigger.

38:25.128 --> 38:27.653
And Lewis,

38:27.696 --> 38:31.047
killed in police custody.

38:33.485 --> 38:35.225
I knew when those cops--

38:35.269 --> 38:36.749
when they showed up
in my classroom, I knew,

38:36.792 --> 38:39.142
and yet,
I led them right to him.

38:41.667 --> 38:43.364
[exhales sharply]

38:43.408 --> 38:44.409
I should've known
they'd follow me.

38:44.452 --> 38:47.368
It was so, so stupid.

38:47.412 --> 38:49.065
You know, and then I got
you involved,

38:49.109 --> 38:52.112
and I probably made things
worse for him.

38:52.155 --> 38:53.766
I didn't protect him.

38:56.072 --> 38:58.336
They didn't protect him.

39:04.646 --> 39:07.301
You know what
burns me the most?

39:08.737 --> 39:09.782
- What?

39:12.393 --> 39:16.397
- I heard Lewis
was riding in a patrol car

39:16.441 --> 39:18.573
with two Black officers.

39:22.272 --> 39:24.405
- How'd you hear that?

39:24.449 --> 39:26.625
- Witnesses on the street.

39:30.672 --> 39:35.373
How do they sleep at night
knowing that Lewis died

39:35.416 --> 39:37.549
sitting right next to them?

39:39.638 --> 39:42.075
- I don't know.

39:49.735 --> 39:52.564
- Why are you
looking at me like that?

39:54.435 --> 39:55.697
- [whispering]
Celeste.

39:58.831 --> 40:01.094
I gotta tell you.

40:03.401 --> 40:05.098
I'm sorry, but I--
- No, no, no.

40:05.141 --> 40:06.752
No, no, you don't do that,
okay?

40:09.494 --> 40:11.583
You're not doing that.

40:11.626 --> 40:13.411
You don't apologize to me.

40:16.457 --> 40:19.329
None of this is on you, okay?

40:19.373 --> 40:22.376
You tried to help, and I
appreciate that so, so much.

40:22.420 --> 40:24.422
I really do, I really do.

40:28.600 --> 40:32.473
I think you

40:32.517 --> 40:35.128
are a very good man, Kevin.

40:39.219 --> 40:42.265
Okay, can we just--

40:46.226 --> 40:47.357
Can we just have some beers

40:47.401 --> 40:51.144
and just sit in silence
together?

40:51.187 --> 40:54.408
Our own little safe space?

40:54.452 --> 40:56.889
Is that okay?

40:56.932 --> 40:58.281
Yeah?

41:01.981 --> 41:04.287
You coming?

41:04.331 --> 41:11.338
♪

41:21.914 --> 41:24.873
[suspenseful music]

41:24.917 --> 41:31.924
♪

41:51.987 --> 41:55.208
[wolf howls]
